-- Copper Climbs a Second Day in London and Shanghai, Leading Gains in Metals
-- B y   H e l e n   S u n
-- 2010-12-20T01:07:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/copper-climbs-a-second-day-in-london-and-shanghai-leading-gains-in-metals.html
Copper advanced for a second day
from London to Shanghai, leading an advance in industrial
metals. Copper for three-month delivery on the London Metal
Exchange gained 1.7 percent to $9,220 a metric ton, while the
March-delivery contract on the Shanghai Futures Exchange climbed
1.4 percent to 69,370 yuan ($10,408) a ton.  Zinc on the LME jumped 2.2 percent to $2,324 a ton, while
lead rose 1.2 percent to $2,448 a ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Sun in Shanghai at 
 hsun30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Oakley at 
 moakley@bloomberg.net  